               <floruit notBefore="1883" notAfter="1942">He was an important Eritrean Catholic scholar.
                  He joined the Catholic Seminary of <placeName ref="LOC4002Karan"/> in <date>1883</date>.
                  In <date>1893</date>,
                  he was ordained in <placeName ref="LOC4002Karan"/> by <persName ref="PRS3231Crouzet"/> and became parish priest in <placeName ref="LOC3754HalibM"/>. 
                  In the following years, he became an active missionary who introduced Catholicism in his native area <placeName ref="LOC5620SebSal"/>. In <date>1899</date>, Takla Māryām was the delegate of the Vicariate of <placeName ref="Q986"/> to the worldwide exposition hosted in
                  <placeName ref="Q495"/>. In <date>1910</date>, he was transferred to <placeName ref="LOC3957Jerusa"/> 
               </floruit>
               <death when="1942">He died at <placeName ref="Q220"/> in <date>1942</date>.</death>
                  
                  
